    "body": "The `.gitignore` system allows filtering of which files get picked up by `git add`, but not of which files get picked up by `git add --force`.\r\n\r\nThe `spec` config is a similar file filter, and you are debating whether the files passed as CLI arguments should have this filter applied or not.  So you could make it so that the filter *is* applied by default, but not if an additional `--force` option is specified.",
