    "body": "Hey @aspiers!\r\n\r\nThanks for creating this issue and digging this deep on it.\r\n\r\n> 4. The user set a spec and passed some files: ???\r\n\r\nI mostly think that we should do what mocha does. It runs everything that's covered by the `spec` and the file. I just tried it in a new project.\r\n\r\nI have a few questions though:\r\n\r\n1. Does it work out of the box if we don't call any `addFile`? I believe that's part of the CLI \"part\" of mocha, and not really exported by the library interface. Take a look at [this file](https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/blob/34643e4c0821aeb8d6977c1942bc106c9363789a/lib/cli/collect-files.js#L25).\r\n2. If we want to behave like mocha, or if it doesn't work out of the box, would we need to implement this \"collect-files\" functionality ourselves? Or can we use that file?",
